cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Comicast in academic or industry work, please cite it as below."
title: "Comicast: AI audiobook generator for digital comics with per-character voices"
abstract: >-
  Comicast is an end-to-end pipeline that converts a digital comic
  (CBZ / CBR / PDF) into an audiobook with per-character voices.
  The architecture combines a 3-pass vision-language model attribution
  stage (cast extraction, per-page bubble attribution, narrative
  consistency check), a confidence-gated human-in-the-loop review,
  cross-volume series memory for in-context learning, and a
  cost-bounded budget guard. To our knowledge it is the first publicly
  released pipeline that addresses comic-to-audiobook generation with
  these properties; the closest prior work (arXiv:2509.15253, Sept
  2025) reports automated attribution accuracy without HITL or release.
